{
  "texts": [
    "By comparing the perplexity of each masked sentence P P L -i with the original perplexity P P L ori, we calculate a relative perplexity ratio r i for masked sentence:r i = P P L -i P P L original (4)This ratio quantifies the extent to which replacing each word w i with a mask decreases the sentence's overall perplexity.",
    "A significant decrease in perplexity (i.e., a lower r i) indicates that the word w i likely contributes to the nonsensical nature of the sentence.",
    "The word associated with the minimum ratio r min is identified as the primary nonsensical concept:c nonsensical = arg min w i r i(5)This approach allows us to effectively isolate the specific element in the sentence that causes the entire sentence to contradict commonsense knowledge.",
    "Knowledge-aware promptingAfter identifying the nonsensical concept, the next stage in our framework is knowledgeaware prompting, which encompasses both knowledge grounding and explanation generation.",
    "These steps are carried out in succession to produce an accurate explanation addressing the statement's commonsense contradiction."
  ]
}